<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <title>Error Pages Demo — Salata</title>
    <style>
        body { font-family: sans-serif; max-width: 600px; margin: 40px auto; padding: 0 20px; color: #333; }
        code { background: #f0f0f0; padding: 2px 6px; border-radius: 3px; }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Error Pages Demo</h1>
    <p>This is a working page. Try visiting a non-existent URL to see the custom 404 page.</p>
    <p>The config for this example points <code>page_404</code> and <code>page_500</code> to custom <code>.slt</code> error templates.</p>
    <python>
from datetime import datetime
print(f"<p>Page generated at: {datetime.now().strftime('%H:%M:%S')}</p>")
    </python>
</body>
</html>
